# TypeScript Standards for mcp-5etools

- Enable strict mode (see [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)).
- Avoid `any` in public types; use precise interfaces and generics.
- Favor small, composable functions with explicit return types for public APIs.
- Prefer pure utilities in `src/` for rendering logic and tag handling.
- Match existing project formatting; avoid refactors that only change formatting.
